<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="586" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,710,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1829,1854]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Remarks</emphasis>
. The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang &amp; Saigusa, 2001" authorityName="Yang &amp; Saigusa" authorityYear="2001" box="[810,1272,1829,1854]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Rhaphium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhongdianum">
<emphasis box="[810,997,1829,1853]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">R. zhongdianum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yang" box="[1008,1272,1829,1854]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" refString="Yang, D. &amp; Saigusa, T. (2001) New and little known species of Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from China (IX). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique Entomologie, 71, 165 - 188." type="journal article" year="2001">Yang &amp; Saigusa, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Yunnan province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[291,361,1865,1890]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">China</collectingCountry>
, but may be separated from the latter by the length / width ratio of the first flagellomere, the color of legs and the shape of the cercus. In 
<taxonomicName box="[656,839,1901,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Rhaphium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhongdianum">
<emphasis box="[656,839,1901,1925]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">R. zhongdianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the first flagellomere is 8.0 times longer than wide; the legs are mainly yellow, but the mid and hind coxae are black except the extreme apex; the cercus is deeply bifurcated with 2 long lobes (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang" box="[479,736,1973,1998]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" refString="Yang, D. &amp; Saigusa, T. (2001) New and little known species of Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from China (IX). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique Entomologie, 71, 165 - 188." type="journal article" year="2001">Yang &amp; Saigusa, 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1338,2009,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,710,2034]" box="[199,1338,2009,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,2009,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Etymology</emphasis>
. The word ‘ 
<emphasis box="[464,565,2009,2033]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">bilobum’</emphasis>
means bifoliate. The new species is named after the shape of cercus.
</paragraph>
